<TITLE> HSCs to go ahead in all areas </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr(bdnews24.com)The education ministry said Saturday that the HSC and equivalent examinations would be held on Sunday as scheduled, as there was no great fallout reported in the southeastern cyclone-hit districts. "Students are asked not to be confused about the exam schedule," ministry spokesperson Sabud Chandra Dali told bdnews24.com. Education ministry officials were assigned on Friday to look in to calls and be prepared for possible rescheduling of exams in cyclone-hit areas. "After receiving situation reports from the deputy commissioners of the Bijli-hit districts, the board authorities have decided to continue all exams on schedule," said Dali on Saturday. "The second English paper will be held tomorrow (Sunday) as per the schedule," he added. b
